steps.instruction: Slice half a pound of thick-cut bacon into three-quarter inch pieces.
Turn the pan on to medium heat.
Add a tiny bit of olive oil to the pan.
Break the sliced bacon into the pan.
Render the fat from the bacon until crispy.
Season four quarts of boiling pasta water with a tablespoon of kosher salt.
Grate three ounces each of Pecorino Romano and Parmigiano Reggiano cheese.
Mix three whole eggs and two egg yolks in a bowl.
Whisk the grated cheese into the egg mixture.
Add fresh ground black pepper to the egg mixture and whisk it in.
Add a quarter cup of boiling pasta water to the egg mixture and whisk quickly.
Drop the spaghetti into the boiling water and cook for about 10 minutes until slightly al dente.
Turn off the heat and drain most of the bacon fat, leaving about two tablespoons in the pan.
Transfer the cooked spaghetti to the pan with the bacon fat using tongs.
Add the egg and cheese mixture to the spaghetti in the pan.
Gently mix the spaghetti with the egg and cheese mixture to avoid scrambling the eggs.
Add a little pasta water if the sauce is too thick to loosen it up.
Plate the pasta and top with more Parmigiano Reggiano and crispy bacon.

steps.instruction: Toast black peppercorns over medium-low heat until fragrant.
Move peppercorns around to ensure even toasting.
Remove peppercorns from heat after the first pop sound.
Let toasted peppercorns cool on a tray.
Crush cooled peppercorns using a pan with body weight pressure.
Grate Parmesan and Pecorino cheese using a microplane.
Set eggs on the counter for 30 minutes to reach room temperature.
Crack three whole eggs and separate two egg yolks.
Mix eggs and grated cheese to form a smooth mixture.
Add toasted black peppercorns to the egg and cheese mixture.
Cut guanciale into large matchstick-sized pieces.
Add salt to boiling water until it is sea salty.
Cook dry spaghetti pasta in boiling water for about 10 minutes.
Heat olive oil in a pan before adding guanciale.
Cook guanciale until light golden brown, ensuring it remains chewy.
Stir pasta occasionally to prevent sticking.
Taste pasta to ensure it is al dente before removing from heat.
Mix pasta with egg and cheese mixture in a bowl, not a pan.
Add guanciale and its fat to the pasta mixture and mix well.
Serve pasta with additional guanciale, black pepper, and cheese on top.
